      • close

        public void close()
        Description copied from interface: Consumer
        Closes the message consumer, rendering it unusable.

        Once closed, an application acquires a new instance in order to continue to receive messages.

        New messages will not be processed and delivered after a call to close() returns, although it is possible for a single asynchronous message delivery to occur if it has already begun when close() is called.

        Specified by:
        close in interface Consumer
        Specified by:
        close in interface Closeable

      • close

        public void close(boolean linger)
        Description copied from interface: FlowReceiver
        [SolReserved] Close a flow, optionally signaling a non-durable Endpoint should linger on the appliance. When linger is set, the Endpoint will not be destroyed immediately, but rather only after a appliance-defined timeout. Unacknowledged messages on the Endpoint will be preserved during this time.
        Specified by:
        close in interface FlowReceiver
        Parameters:
        linger - If true, and this flow is bound to a non-durable Endpoint, signals to the appliance the Endpoint should not be immediately destroyed.

      • receive

        public BytesXMLMessage receive(int timeoutInMillis)
                        throws JCSMPException
        Description copied from interface: Consumer
        Receives the next available message. If no message is available, this method blocks until timeoutInMillis is reached. A timeout of zero never expires, and the call blocks indefinitely.

        Specified by:
        receive in interface Consumer
        Parameters:
        timeoutInMillis - The timeout in milliseconds.
        Returns:
        The next available message, or null if the timeout expires.
        Throws:
        InvalidOperationException - If the consumer is not started, or a message listener is set.
        JCSMPTransportException - If the consumer was closed after the method was called, but before any message was received.
        JCSMPException

        public Destination getDestination()
        Description copied from interface: FlowReceiver
        Returns the Destination to which messages should be published to get routed to this flow's bound Endpoint.

        • If bound to a TopicEndpoint, the Destination will be of type Topic.
        • If bound to a Queue, the Destination will be of type Queue.
        • If bound to a SubscriberEndpoint, this method returns null.
        Specified by:
